[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-7)

Content that should be repeated on each page in the output document, is called static page content.

For such content, XSL-FO provides four page areas - top (header), bottom (footer), left and right. The Business Designer supports the easy insertion of content into these areas (see figure below).

To fill **static page areas **such as headers and footers, use the *Static Page Content *view, switch to this view by clicking the![](data:image/png;base64,) icon in the top right corner.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

In the outline you can see that there are the elements for the areas "Header", "Footer", "Left" and "Right". Drag the desired element into the respective area element.

> Note

*For the left/right area this works best if you drag the elements into the outline, for the header and footer you can also drag them directly into the page.*

To insert **page numbers **drag a *Page Number *element into the static area.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

By default, this element generates the current page number. If the total page number is required, set the page-number attribute to "last" `Style &amp; Properties &gt; Advanced &gt; Miscellaneous`. You can add the desired text or spacing between the elements.

Example: to create page numbers in the form of "Page 1 of 4", insert the page number element twice, leave the default option ("current") for the first element and set the "last" option for the second element. Insert a text element with "of" (german screenshot: "von") in between.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

*If you want to omit the page number on the first page, a complex Page Master is required - see Chapter *[*Page break, page settings, page master.*](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-business-designer-user-guide-page-break-page-settings-page-master)
